fields.description:
[v1.1] Deed of Variation — Consideration Extraction Prompt


Objective
Extract consideration provisions that are added, varied, or removed by this Deed of Variation.

Return strict JSON matching the Consideration Schema.

Extract only consideration provisions that this deed changes.

Do not extract consideration provisions that are merely recited for background.

Do not reconstruct the original lease consideration regime.

Record only the amendments evidenced by this document.

If the deed does not amend any consideration provision:



{
  "consideration": [],
  "rent_model_terms": [],
  "contingent_consideration": []
}
Core Principle
A Deed of Variation modifies an existing lease.

The extraction must capture:

new consideration obligations;

amended consideration obligations;

removed consideration obligations;

new rent mechanisms;

amended rent mechanisms;

removed rent mechanisms;

new contingent consideration mechanisms;

amended contingent consideration mechanisms;

removed contingent consideration mechanisms.

The extraction must not capture:

original provisions repeated for context;

historical provisions;

unchanged provisions.

Extract the amendment.

Ignore the recital.

Classification Rules
Before extracting, classify the provision into the correct top-level array.

consideration
Use for fixed payment obligations only.

Examples:

rent;

ground rent;

base rent;

peppercorn rent;

premium;

reverse premium;

landlord contribution;

licence fee.

rent_model_terms
Use for rent or licence fee calculation mechanisms.

Examples:

turnover rent;

percentage rent;

indexation;

CPI rent;

RPI rent;

formula rent;

arithmetic progression;

stepped rent structures;

umbrella totals.

contingent_consideration
Use for contingent, deferred, variable or event-triggered consideration.

Examples:

overage;

clawback;

uplift;

profit share;

development gain;

planning gain;

additional consideration;

further consideration.

Never place these mechanisms in consideration or rent_model_terms.

Three Possible Outcomes
Every extracted record must represent one of the following outcomes.

Addition
The deed introduces a new consideration provision.

Populate:



"consideration_change_type": "addition"
and



"targets_consideration_description": ""
Populate all remaining fields with the new terms.

Variation
The deed changes an existing consideration provision.

Examples:

rent amount changed;

turnover percentage changed;

overage trigger changed;

indexation mechanism changed;

stepped rent schedule changed.

Populate:



"consideration_change_type": "variation"
and:



"targets_consideration_description"
with a concise description of the original provision being amended.

The record must contain the complete revised provision.

Do not output only the changed fields.

Removal
The deed removes an existing consideration provision.

Examples:

rent deleted;

turnover rent removed;

overage removed;

clawback removed.

Populate:



"consideration_change_type": "removal"
and:



"targets_consideration_description"
with a description of the provision being removed.

Populate sufficient identifying information for chain matching.

Removed provisions are not current provisions.

Fixed Consideration Rules
For records extracted into:



"consideration"
apply all standard Consideration schema rules.

Extract:

consideration_type;

payment_amount;

currency;

condition;

amount_basis;

payment_frequency;

payment_timing;

payment_dates;

payment_start_date;

payment_end_date;

rent_commencement_date.

Never calculate amounts.

Never derive dates.

Use printed information only.

Rent Model Term Rules
For records extracted into:



"rent_model_terms"
extract:

term_type;

mechanism_summary;

currency;

fixed_amount_printed;

requires_external_inputs;

external_inputs.

Extract the complete revised mechanism.

Do not output only the amended wording.

Contingent Consideration Rules
For records extracted into:



"contingent_consideration"
extract:

consideration_type;

mechanism;

mechanism_summary;

trigger_event;

currency;

fixed_amount_printed;

requires_external_inputs;

external_inputs;

condition.

Do not calculate contingent payments.

Do not determine whether trigger events have occurred.

Extract only the mechanism described in the deed.

Stepped Rent
Where the deed introduces multiple rent phases:

Create one consideration record per phase.

If an existing rent is replaced:



"consideration_change_type": "variation"
on every phase.

If a completely new stepped structure is introduced:



"consideration_change_type": "addition"
on every phase.

Routing Boundaries
This extraction owns consideration only.

Do not extract:

Topic

Owner

Service Charge

Service Charge

Insurance

Insurance

Deposit

Deposit

Break Rights

Breaks

Notice Requirements

Notice Requirements

Alienation

Alienation

Guarantee Liabilities

Guarantee & Indemnity

Repair Obligations

Repair & Maintenance

Full Document Scan
Review the entire deed.

Consideration amendments may appear within:

operative clauses;

schedules;

amendment provisions;

substitution provisions;

deletion provisions;

supplemental clauses;

appendices.

Do not rely solely on clause headings.

Evidence Rules
Every extracted record must contain:



"internal_source"
and



"internal_evidence"
Use the structured evidence format required by the schema.

Evidence must:

be verbatim;

directly support the amendment;

directly support the payment or mechanism;

directly support the addition, variation or removal.

Use the minimum evidence necessary.

Interpretation Rules
Extract only what this deed changes.

Never infer:

amounts;

frequencies;

triggers;

percentages;

formulae;

external inputs;

contingent events.

Where wording is unclear:

preserve the uncertainty;

do not resolve ambiguity;

do not guess.

Deed of Variation Rules
Rule

Requirement

consideration_change_type

Never original

Addition

New provision introduced

Variation

Existing provision amended

Removal

Existing provision deleted

Recitals

Ignore

Unchanged provisions

Do not extract

Variation records

Complete replacement records

Removed provisions

Not current provisions

Output Rules
Return strict JSON only.

No commentary.

No explanations.

No legal analysis.

No summaries.

Output must conform exactly to the Consideration Schema v1.4.
